name: Warung Laota
address: Pertokoan Niaga Nusa Dua, Puri Mumbul, Jl. Bypass Ngurah Rai No.77x, Jimbaran, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1: Famous chinese food restaurant in Bali, they serve halal food only. The food is good, we ordered the porridge (or congee), the cereal prawn, the sapo tofu and the steamed snapper. They are all delicious, the snapper is on the pricey side though so beware before ordering. However the service is a bit slow, it takes forever everytime we ask for something like additional utensils or other things.
review 2: It's a great place. My family and I ordered a lot of food. The official recommended several dishes and they were all delicious. We liked everything we tried, especially the beef in black pepper sauce, it was soft
review 3: I would say one of the best places to eat in Bali. I generally love local cuisine more when I travel, but I dare say I do not regret coming here. The dimsum was great, especially the Xiao Long Bao. I also loved the Lemonade sauce chicken. If you are on your way to the airport, visit this place!
review 4: Very tasty food. Limited vegetarian options. All items didn‚Äôt comes with cup of steamed rise, so have to order for steamed rice separately. Soft drink was served too late without any reason and have to remind few times. Additional car park available on next door.
review 5:
We stopped for lunch, but some menus weren't available. Yes, it's a popular place, but it was quite warm.
The duck was delicious, hakau also good. My friends love the congee.
Too bad when we asked for the bill, they didn't give us one order that was billed. Fortunately, we checked and asked for the missed meal to be take-out.
The toilet could use maintenance since the flush didn't work.

name: Alindra Villas & Spa
address: Jl. Bypass Ngurah Rai Jl. Aneka Warga No.12, Jimbaran, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80363, Indonesia
review 1:
Accommodation: Comfortable, spacious, value for money
Staff: Friendly, attentive, courteous
Complimentary Breakfast: Limited to selected menu items, but portion size is very good and delicious
Wedding Venue: Terracotta Garden is very spacious, allowing various setup options. It rained during our wedding reception and we were allowed to use the restaurant instead. The landscape is beautiful so we could take gorgeous wedding pictures & videos.
Location: Quite hidden from main road, providing a quaint surrounding but still accessible for guests who are not staying in the villa
review 2:
The place is silent, peaceful and the garden makes it special.
Our room was big and toilet amazing.

It was full of mosquitoes, in the garden and in our room. They know it so they provide an anti mosquito spray and other tools. Despite the huge number of mosquitoes, they did not bother us.

Breakfast was good. But they apply taxes and service percentages to the extra beverages you ask for without informing.

The staff were good. We rented a scooter because the location is bad and you need one to go around. There are not other scooters renter near by. The helmets were all huge, the motorcycle did not work properly and they asked us 140k that is a lot. Massages are also overpriced.
review 3: It was the best out of all the accommodations I tried in bali. We were warmly welcomed with drinks, and the entrance to the villas was magnificent with their ethnic pool getting all its attention. Our package had breakfast included, so I would say the price was OK. They also have scooters, so u can hire one if you want to go out and check the area. The staff was great, all of them ‚ù§Ô∏è. They had their own spa but unfortunately I couldnt try it myslef but I'm sure it must be well up to standard. Overall, the villa looks luxurious and the service was great. One of my favs..üçπ
review 4:
This resort and Spa was amazing.
There was so much privacy as many rooms had their own private pools. The grounds are immaculate, and the staff so super friendly and helpful. I highly recommend this accommodation. We stayed for 8 nights.
The Spa treatments were fabulous too! Had massage and facial which were great!
review 5:
This h√¥tel IS marvelous, WE enjoy the place, the room, th√© private pool and the disponibility of the hotel staff.
The d√©coration of the h√¥tel IS really beautiful and peaceful. The architect did a really good job to mix a peaceful place and all the ergonomy. The staff is reactive for any question and need. A sp√©cial thank to  spa service of the h√¥tel who IS really nice and calm, the balinese massage and hot stone was the best i ever did.

name: Jaansan Bali Restaurant
address: Jl. Bypass Ngurah Rai No.96-B, Jimbaran, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1: This is a must for any trip to Bali and worth the journey.  Best food our whole trip and we returned multiple times.  Eat the Bebek (duck- we like it grilled), Nasi, their seafood platters, which are all absolutely delicious. Very good portions, and good price and value. Maaday arta, the owner, personally meets you and we quickly became friends. The staff is very efficient and friendly.
review 2: I went for a cocktail free flow promotion. The manager paired my cocktails according to my meal, Ayam sambal bawang. He paired the cocktail to match my meal. Starting from sweet and chill and then more intense to match the meal and tapered it off to a dessert taste. Awesome. EXTREMELY AWESOME. He was aware of my progress and kept the drinks different and coming. Very attentive, warm and friendly. ‚ù§Ô∏èü©∑üß°üíõüíöüíôü©µüíúü§éüñ§ü©∂ü§ç awesome awesome experience. I'm so happy.
review 3: Friendly service, we ordered seafood set, bebek (duck) and mee goreng with chicken. when we informed that the soup was salty, they immediately wanted to rectify by changing another bowl of soup, but we declined. The duck was very good and moist unlike other places I‚Äôve eaten at that is dry and overcooked. The fish was fresh, and mee goreng was yummy!
review 4: The fried duck dish is great with crispy skin and juicy meat. The grill prawn is fresh but I do not enjoy the sauce they put. I think the prawns would have tasted better with just salt and pepper. Do bring along a insect repellent as there are lotsa mosquitoes.
review 5:
"Jaansan Bali Restaurant offers a culinary experience like no other. The food is a true delight, bursting with rich, authentic flavors that will leave you craving more. What's more, its proximity to the beach is a definite plus. With careful planning, you can even catch a breathtaking sunset just a short 5-minute walk away after enjoying your meal."

"Jaansan Bali Restaurant is a true gem, not only for its delectable cuisine but also for its convenient location near the beach. Imagine enjoying a fantastic meal and then taking a leisurely stroll to witness a stunning sunset. It's a magical combination that's hard to beat. The only downside was the presence of flies, which was a bit of an annoyance when enjoying the meal."

"Jaansan Bali Restaurant's food is a testament to the culinary expertise of the chefs. The added bonus of being a stone's throw away from the beach, where you can catch a breathtaking sunset, adds an extra layer of charm to the dining experience. While the presence of flies was a minor inconvenience, the overall experience was truly memorable."

address: Jl. Bypass Ngurah Rai Gg. Taman Sari No.8, Jimbaran, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1:
A very nice place for a short vacation. We booked for 3 days and extended another three days due to their excellent service. Easy access to Nusa Dua, uluwatu, Denpasar.

Nice spacious rooms, spacious kitchen, excellent service.
review 2: After my experience with VIDI, I can say that it was my best place in Bali. The apartments are spacious, with a kitchen, fridge and freezer, a living room with a TV, as well as the bedroom, which in my case had access to the terrace with a beautiful view of the entire hotel with the pool. Every day I had the opportunity to have my room cleaned. The cleaning of the room is excellent, the cleaning is of high quality. The breakfast I had as part of my stay was very good and the portion was always large. It was possible to choose breakfast from three sets of meals, where together it was roughly possible to choose from about 18 variants of breakfast and various other combinations. As for the approach to the guest - let's say it in two words - absolutelly great! Immediately after my arrival, the best worker Mrs. Putu Diva and her team took care of me and made my whole stay very very pleasant and helped me arrange a lot of things or give advice. Many thanks to the entire VIDI Boutique hotel team. I will remember you and I believe that we have not seen each other for the last time. Ondrej Marek
